17:25.310 --> 17:27.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For that, I'm joined by R.P.
Eddy.

17:27.379 --> 17:31.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He served on the staff of the
National Security
Council during the Clinton
administration,

17:31.450 --> 17:33.419 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
where he worked closely with
British officials.

17:33.452 --> 17:39.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he is the author, along with
Richard Clarke,
of "Warnings: Finding Cassandras
to Stop Catastrophes."

17:39.525 --> 17:41.794 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
R.P. Eddy, thanks very much for
being here.

17:41.827 --> 17:48.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I wonder if you could just start
off telling
us the distinctions that U.K.
intelligence

17:48.233 --> 17:52.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and terror officials have as
