17:52.204 --> 17:55.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
R.P. EDDY, Former National
Security Council
Staff Member: Well, overall,
it's a fairly

17:55.474 --> 17:56.442 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
similar system.

17:56.475 --> 17:59.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is probably two key
differences.

17:59.044 --> 18:04.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One is, it's easier to open up
investigations
and surveillance on individuals
in the U.K.,

18:04.917 --> 18:08.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
British citizens or others, than
it is in
the United States.

18:08.120 --> 18:10.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The second thing is that we have
an inverted
model.

18:10.322 --> 18:13.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the United States -- for
example, here,
I'm sitting in New York City.

18:13.225 --> 18:18.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The NYPD would go out and
collect much of
the intelligence about a
terrorist attack,

18:18.263 --> 18:24.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
potential terrorist attack, and
then the FBI
would make the arrest, depending
on the maturity

18:24.670 --> 18:26.805 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the intelligence collection
in the city.

18:26.839 --> 18:29.308 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In London, in the U.K., it's
opposite.

18:29.341 --> 18:34.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Metropolitan Police Service
or the local
police would actually do the
arresting, where

18:34.379 --> 18:37.616 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MI5 and MPS would do the
intelligence gathering.

18:37.649 --> 18:42.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the key difference is, it's
easier to
begin surveillance on people of
concern.

18:42.521 --> 18:48.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And the U.K.,
