19:19.525 --> 19:21.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So they addressed their
terrorism threat and
got over some of their learnings
earlier than

19:21.860 --> 19:23.562 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
we did.

19:23.595 --> 19:26.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Even so, with
all those
tools, it's clear that the U.K.
officials

19:26.798 --> 19:28.734 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
missed this particular plot.

19:28.767 --> 19:35.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it seems to me that this is
just an indication
of how difficult it is to
identify individuals

19:35.407 --> 19:39.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or maybe a group of individuals
who are trying
to plot quietly these types of
attacks.

19:39.945 --> 19:43.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
R.P. EDDY: Well, let's say
there's probably
two big reasons for that.

19:43.615 --> 19:45.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The first one is technological.

19:45.417 --> 19:49.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And you have heard a number of
U.S. government
officials and British government
officials

19:49.588 --> 19:53.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
