years bemoan the
fact that it's much easier now
to encrypt

19:53.892 --> 19:58.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
your communications on your cell
phone or
over the Internet to a
military-grade level

19:58.063 --> 19:59.932 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
than it used to be.

19:59.965 --> 20:04.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, in some instances, we're
blind as we try
to do collection on those
signals intelligence.

20:04.436 --> 20:07.472 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So that's the first reason that
it's a little
harder, or much harder.

20:07.506 --> 20:10.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The second reason is, ISIS is
different than
al-Qaida.

20:10.142 --> 20:14.713 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, part of why they're
different is, they're
interested in -- or they're more
willing to

20:14.746 --> 20:21.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
allow or to foster what you
would call retail
attacks, small attacks by lone
wolves or people

20:21.320 --> 20:26.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who are just sort of getting
converted into
extremism by ISIS, whereas
al-Qaida, as we

20:26.959 --> 20:32.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
know, is more interested in
large-scale attacks,
taking down huge buildings,
blowing up embassies,

20:32.497 --> 20:34.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
doing things simultaneously.

20:34.333 --> 20:38.770 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So the latter model, the
al-Qaida, is easier
to find, requires more planning,
and, of course,

20:38.804 --> 20:41.106 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
requires larger cells, requires
more training.

20:41.139 --> 20:46.445 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The ISIS model, of being an idea
of mass destruction,
is much harder to catch.

20:46.478 --> 20:49.514 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Someone can be just converted
into extremism
over the Internet.

20:49.548 --> 20:54.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They don't even have to meet
anybody, and
they can go off and carry out
smaller, harder-to-surveil,

20:54.820 --> 20:57.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
harder-to-stop terrorist
attacks.

